snippet.textDisplay:
Korean here. These are the most healthy looking jjajangmyeon and jjampong ive ever seen.

Here are some facts that might interest you:
Jjajangmyeon and jjampong are commonly regarded as cheap unhealthy food.
Most koreans think that jjajangmyeon and jjampong originated from China but its kinda like panda express in the US. They are "chinese style" but it actually made in korea.
Most "chinese restaurants" in korea deliveres food via motorcycles to literally anywhere. I've onced ordered it from under a random bridge on a rainy day. Food showed up 30 minutes later.

snippet.textDisplay:
(Jesus warning about HELL FIRE):


And if thy hand causes you to sin,
cut it off:


it is better for thee
to enter into life maimed,


than having two hands
to go into hell,
into the fire


that never shall be quenched:
Where their worm dieth not,
and the fire is not quenched.


(Mark 9:43-44).


***(Cut if off): Should be taken figuratively; it means to take whatever drastic action is necessary to avoid sin.


***The imagery of Hell (Frequently called gehenna) comes from a garbage dump outside the walls of Jerusalem. Jesus hearers were familiar with the smoldering fires that always burned there.


***(((Obedience))) and (((self-control))) are necessary to overcome sin.


***The longing of the disciples for greatness needed to be reshaped according to God's purposes.

You wasted the neoguri powder, by putting it in while cooking the noodles. You're suppose put it along with the chapagetti powder after you drained most (not all) of the water.

When cooking neoguri, yes you put it in while cooking the noodles, but it's not the same for ram-don recipe.

Side note, you don't have have use all of the neoguri powder you can add according to how spicy you like it, if the noodles come out too thick or dry cause you drained too much water. Just add a couple of ounces of hot water until it is right.

I can’t speak to the Korean pronunciations, but we do need to work on your Japanese ingredient pronunciation.

A = ah, pAHnko, or how you already say the A in dashi
I = ee, mEErEEn, mirin
O = oh, pAHnkOH
U = ooh, dOHnbOOHrrEE (donburri)
E = eh, tAHbEHmOHnOH (tabemono or food)

These are the only things that I have a single issue with in any of your videos. Other than that, KEEP FRICKING KILLING IT SON. ❤️
